<subSubSection pageId="77" pageNumber="1416" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="77.[178,1085,612,723]" pageId="77" pageNumber="1416">
This species-rich and widely distributed group was defined in 
<bibRefCitation author="LOBL I." box="[842,975,612,635]" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse Zool" pageId="77" pageNumber="1416" pagination="727 - 799" part="77" refString="LOBL I. (1970 b): Revision der palaarktischen Arten der Gattungen Scaphisoma LEACH und Caryoscapha GANGLBAUER der Tribus Scaphisomini (Col. Scaphidiidae). - Revue suisse Zool. 77: 727 - 799." title="Revision der palaarktischen Arten der Gattungen Scaphisoma LEACH und Caryoscapha GANGLBAUER der Tribus Scaphisomini (Col. Scaphidiidae)" type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="b">LÖBL 1970b</bibRefCitation>
: 732. It is characterized by a trilobed and symmetrical median lobe, the parameres lacking lobes and symmetrical, in combination with a complex internal sac. The members of the group usually share strigulate abdominal microsculpture and have elytra lacking basal striae.
</paragraph>
